[SN]TITLE[SN]
Four injured in Brighton balcony collapse

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four people were injured, two of them seriously, after a balcony they were standing on collapsed in Brighton.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fire crews called to a property in Montpelier Road just before midnight found part of the stone balcony and its iron railing missing.
Some of those injured had fallen into a basement below.
A Sussex Police spokesman said there were no suspicious circumstances. Building control officials have been examining the scene.
